      <section id="view-architecture" class="view searchable" data-name="Architecture">
        <article class="card">
          <h2>Reference Architecture (Layers 0–7)</h2>
          <p class="muted">Purpose-built for Signals → Plays → Packages → Motions.</p>
          <p>
            <button id="expandLayers" class="btn">Expand all</button>
            <button id="collapseLayers" class="btn">Collapse all</button>
          </p>

          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 0 — Data Sources</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> aggregate operating and exposure evidence.</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> internal service history, telemetry, supplies, contracts, CRM; external/opt-in identity integration status, compliance tags, dark web/breach exposure, tech stack/cloud initiatives.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> normalized source events.</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Data Engineering.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> opt-in governance for external enrichment.</p></details>
          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 1 — Ingestion + Identity Resolution</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> ETL/ELT and entity resolution across account/site/device/contract/contact.</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> source events.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> AccountGraph.</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Platform Engineering.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> confidence-based identity merges with audit trail.</p></details>
          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 2 — Signal Factory (Feature Store)</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> compute security posture, AI/workflow opportunity, and IT propensity signals.</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> AccountGraph + events.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> Signal objects (value/timestamp/source/confidence/decay_rate).</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Data Science.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> freshness windows and drift checks.</p></details>
          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 3 — Scoring &amp; Decisioning</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> produce Security Risk, AI Automation Potential, IT Services Propensity and Play Fit Score (Fit, Readiness, Confidence, Value estimate).</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> Signal portfolio.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> next best plays + why now + proof to gather.</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Decisioning Team.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> explainable ranking and threshold governance.</p></details>
          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 4 — Offer &amp; Bundle Composer</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> map plays to buyable packages.</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> ranked plays, pricing rules.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> Secure Essentials, Secure + Automate, SecureAI Managed bundles.</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Product + Commercial Ops.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> SKU/term guardrails.</p></details>
          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 5 — Orchestration &amp; Workflow</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> route tasks and execute 30-day micro-campaign sprints.</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> play selection and package intent.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> tasks, meetings, proposals, escalations.</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Revenue Operations.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> SLA and escalation rules.</p></details>
          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 6 — Measurement &amp; Learning</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> monitor execution, commercial, and model metrics; reweight signals.</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> outcomes + telemetry.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> threshold updates and targeting improvements.</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Analytics + ML Ops.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> drift and bias checks.</p></details>
          <details class="layer"><summary>Layer 7 — Governance</summary><p><strong>Purpose:</strong> enforce data minimization, segregation, RBAC, audit logs, explainability, partner risk management.</p><p><strong>Inputs:</strong> policy controls and audit events.</p><p><strong>Outputs:</strong> compliance attestations and risk actions.</p><p><strong>Owner:</strong> Security &amp; Compliance.</p><p><strong>Data/Control:</strong> retention and role-based least privilege.</p></details>
        </article>

        <article class="card" style="margin-top:.9rem;">
          <h2>Data Flow</h2>
          <div class="pipeline">
            <span>Sources</span> → <span>Ingestion</span> → <span>Signal Factory</span> → <span>Scoring</span> → <span>Composer</span> → <span>Orchestration</span> → <span>Learning</span> → <span>Governance</span>
